SIMPLE: intoxication
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intoxication
<hw>In*tox`i*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A poisoning, as by a alcoholic or a narcotic
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being intoxicated or drunk;
inebriation; ebriety; drunkenness; the act of intoxicating or making
drunk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A high excitement of mind; an elation which rises to
enthusiasm, frenzy, or madness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That secret <qex>intoxication</qex> of pleasure.</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Drunkenness; inebriation; inebriety; ebriety;
infatuation; delirium. See <er>Drunkenness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intra-</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
